 of the best Mega Drive games I've ever played\" [92%] - Rich Leadbetter, Mean Machines #10 (July 1991)\n\nTRIVIA\n- Sonic Jam contained the first release of Sonic The Hedgehog that gave Sonic his spin dash move, which returns again in this remake\n- Sonic The Hedgehog was also released in arcades on SEGA's Mega-Tech and Mega Play systems\n - Rabbit and armadillo characters were considered for Sonic before settling on a hedgehog design\n- While \"Eggman\" is Dr. Robotnik's nickname in the West, he has always been known as \"Eggman\" in Japan\n\nCLASSIC GAME FACTS\n- First released in the US on June 23rd, 1991 \n- It took Yuji Naka almost a year to finish designing Green Hill Zone Act 1\n- Spring Yard Zone and Scrap Brain Zone were originally called Sparkling Zone and Clock Work Zone\n- Music composed by Masato Nakamura of Dreams Come True fame\n\n- - - - -\nPrivacy Policy: http://www.sega.com/mprivacy\nTerms of Use: http://www.sega.com/terms\n\nGame apps are ad-supported and no in-app purchases are required to progress; ad-free play option available with in-app purchase.\n\n© SEGA. All rights reserved. SEGA, the SEGA logo, Sonic the Hedgehog, SEGA Forever, and the SEGA Forever logo are registered trademarks or trademarks of SEGA Holdings Co., Ltd. or its affiliates.","rating":80.0,"popularity":1.0,"total_rating":80.0,"total_rating_count":0,"rating_count":0,"games":[36794,36608,34919,51485,22819,40524,51683,24199,23175,16468],"tags":[1,268435489],"category":0,"themes":[1],"genres":[33],"first_release_date":1242864000000,"platforms":[39],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":39,"date":1242864000000,"region":8,"human":"2009-May-21","y":2009,"m":5}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ssgs3livawf1bhfqvbcl.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ssgs3livawf1bhfqvbcl","width":552,"height":414},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/v1tdy7pnkfbe0jyaqxxt.jpg","cloudinary_id":"v1tdy7pnkfbe0jyaqxxt","width":552,"height":414},{"url":"//images.igdb